    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<h2>Rosalin Brent &mdash; Proprietor, The Sign of the Brown Hare</h2><p><em>Mid-fifties; weathered; capable. Half-sister of Haskur Vandrell (same mother, different fathers). Runs the small roadhouse on the South Wool Road two days' ride south of Loftwick. NEW for Phase 2 sidequest &mdash; see the journal <em>Phase 2 &mdash; Sidequest: The Sign of the Brown Hare</em>.</em></p><h3>Quick read</h3><ul><li>Faded auburn hair shot with grey, pulled back in a no-nonsense bun. Strong shoulders, calloused hands, grey-green eyes with a tired but steady directness.</li><li>Plain forest-green wool dress under a cream-and-grey apron; a thin silver Heironeous medallion at the collar (worn for forty years, not on display).</li><li>Has run the Brown Hare since age 24. Owns it outright. Never married.</li></ul><h3>Motive</h3><p>Keep her inn running, her staff fed, and her brother's memory alive in the only way she has left &mdash; by not throwing out the things he left as a boy. She is not actively looking for him. She has long since stopped looking. <em>She is, however, ready for whatever news comes.</em></p><h3>Tell</h3><p>When she is reading someone, she folds her hands flat on the table in front of her and looks at the space between her fingers, not at the person's face. When she has decided something about them, she looks up.</p><h3>What she knows</h3><ul><li>Hask's childhood, in close detail.</li><li>His eight visits home since 551 CY, dated approximately.</li><li>The man with the grey beard who came with him in 575 CY (Aerdy accent, did not give a name, addressed Hask as &ldquo;Andren&rdquo; in the kitchen when he thought she was not listening &mdash; she has remembered the name without understanding it for six years).</li></ul><h3>What she does NOT know</h3><ul><li>Cindren &amp; Vhal. The firm name has never been spoken to her.</li><li>Korre, Kethren, Sereth, &ldquo;E.&rdquo; &mdash; none of these names.</li><li>The under-road, the Aerdy harbor commission, the deep conspiracy.</li><li>That Hask kept her on a map of his caravan routes. She is wounded by this when the party tells her.</li></ul><h3>Useful lines</h3><ul><li><em>&ldquo;Hask was never clever. He was hungry and he was beautiful and he was furious. Someone with a head on their shoulders found him and put work in his hands.&rdquo;</em></li><li><em>&ldquo;The first time he came back he wore a coat that did not fit him. It was a good coat. It was somebody else's good coat.&rdquo;</em></li><li><em>&ldquo;If you find him alive, you may tell him I am still here. That is enough.&rdquo;</em></li><li><em>&ldquo;I do not keep change for gold pieces. You are not in a city.&rdquo;</em></li></ul><h3>Mechanics</h3><p><strong>Statblock: Commoner (CR 0)</strong> with proficiency in Insight (+5) and Perception (+5). Cook's Tools +3. HP 10; AC 10. Noncombatant. If endangered she hides; if protected she returns to work the next morning as if nothing happened.</p><p><em>She is not authorially protected.</em> If the party permits her death &mdash; through carelessness, through neglect, through deliberate act &mdash; she dies. The campaign continues; the never-sent letter is lost; the Phase 6 carry-forward is forfeit. The GM should make this cost felt rather than retconned.</p>",
        "public": ""
